time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

We use a map to store the count of each character in the word. Then, we iterate k times to calculate the total count of possible strings. In each iteration, we multiply the current count by the count of characters in the word. We use bitwise operations to efficiently calculate the count of characters in the word. The time complexity is O(n) because we iterate the word once, and the space complexity is O(n) because we use a map with n elements.

